"use strict";(self.webpackChunkpos_doc=self.webpackChunkpos_doc||[]).push([[146],{8700(e,o,s){s.r(o),s.d(o,{comp:()=>t,data:()=>n});var a=s(641);const r={},t=(0,s(6262).A)(r,[["render",function(e,o){return(0,a.uX)(),(0,a.CE)("div",null,[...o[0]||(o[0]=[(0,a.Fv)('<h1 id="order-management-in-woocommerce-point-of-sale" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#order-management-in-woocommerce-point-of-sale"><span>Order Management in WooCommerce Point of Sale</span></a></h1><p>Efficient order management is a core feature of <strong>WooCommerce Point of Sale (POS)</strong>, allowing POS users to handle sales from product selection to checkout, including customer management, discounts, cart holds, offline orders, and synchronization with the WooCommerce online store.</p><hr><h2 id="processing-pos-orders" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#processing-pos-orders"><span>Processing POS Orders</span></a></h2><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/home-all-5.webp" alt="ManageoutletAndPosUser"></p><p>POS users can manage complete sales activity directly from the panel, including:</p><ul><li>Adding products to the cart</li><li>Adding customer details</li><li>Holding carts for later processing</li><li>Paying for orders</li></ul><p>All these details are accessible and manageable from the POS dashboard.</p><hr><h2 id="adding-products-to-cart" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#adding-products-to-cart"><span>Adding Products to Cart</span></a></h2><p>POS users have multiple methods to add products to the cart:</p><ul><li><strong>Barcode Scanning:</strong> Add products using SKU or Product ID</li><li><strong>Manual Search:</strong> Type the product name in the search bar and add it to the cart</li><li><strong>Category Browsing:</strong> Navigate through product categories and select items</li><li><strong>Custom Products:</strong> Add products not available on the website but present in the physical store</li></ul><h3 id="adding-custom-products" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#adding-custom-products"><span>Adding Custom Products</span></a></h3><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/add-new-custom-product.webp" alt="ManageoutletAndPosUser"></p><ul><li>Click the <strong>plus sign</strong> button</li><li>Enter product details such as name and price</li><li>Click <strong>Add</strong> to include the product in the cart for checkout</li></ul><hr><h2 id="customer-management" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#customer-management"><span>Customer Management</span></a></h2><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/customers-2.webp" alt="ManageoutletAndPosUser"></p><p>After adding products, POS users can manage customer details:</p><ul><li>Select existing customers from the customer field</li><li>Add new customers on-the-fly</li><li>Use the <strong>Default Customer</strong> option for walk-in sales</li><li>Update customer information as needed</li></ul><p>Once a customer is added, their name appears in the cart for reference.</p><hr><h2 id="checkout-process" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#checkout-process"><span>Checkout Process</span></a></h2><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/cash-payment-payable-amount.webp" alt="ManageoutletAndPosUser"></p><p>POS supports multiple payment options:</p><ul><li><strong>Cash Payment:</strong> Direct cash handling</li><li><strong>Card Payment:</strong> Credit/debit card transactions via terminals</li><li><strong>Other Payment Methods:</strong> All admin-configured methods such as PayPal or Sunmi Terminal</li></ul><p><strong>Key Points:</strong></p><ul><li>Monetary transactions are processed outside the POS system; POS records the payment method used</li><li>Split payments are supported (e.g., part cash, part card)</li><li>POS tracks each payment method separately for accurate reconciliation</li></ul><hr><h2 id="applying-coupons-discounts" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#applying-coupons-discounts"><span>Applying Coupons &amp; Discounts</span></a></h2><h3 id="coupons" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#coupons"><span>Coupons</span></a></h3><ul><li>POS users can apply available coupons at checkout</li><li>Enter the coupon code and hit <strong>Apply Coupon</strong></li><li>Coupon application is confirmed via a pop-up and reflected in the cart</li></ul><h3 id="discounts" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#discounts"><span>Discounts</span></a></h3><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/apply-discount-to-sale.webp" alt="ManageoutletAndPosUser"></p><ul><li>Discounts can be applied percentage-wise or as a flat amount</li><li>The <strong>Apply Discount to Sale</strong> option in the cart allows the POS agent to select the type of discount</li><li>The <strong>Grand Total</strong> updates automatically to reflect discounted amounts</li></ul><hr><h2 id="offline-orders" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#offline-orders"><span>Offline Orders</span></a></h2><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/offline-sale-order.webp" alt="ManageoutletAndPosUser"></p><p>Offline sales are stored locally and can be managed as follows:</p><ul><li>Access offline sales under <strong>POS &gt; Order &gt; Offline Sales</strong></li><li>Use the <strong>Sync Order</strong> button to synchronize offline orders with the online store</li><li>Offline functionality works only with <strong>Master Stock Inventory</strong></li></ul><hr><h2 id="order-management-for-admins" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#order-management-for-admins"><span>Order Management for Admins</span></a></h2><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/manageorders.png" alt="ManageoutletAndPosUser"></p><p>Admins can manage orders via <strong>WooCommerce Point of Sale &gt; Orders</strong>:</p><ul><li>View the list of all orders</li><li>Click a specific order (e.g., #211) to access detailed information</li></ul><hr><h2 id="woocommerce-website-orders" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#woocommerce-website-orders"><span>WooCommerce Website Orders</span></a></h2><p>Orders placed on the WooCommerce website are visible in the POS:</p><ul><li>POS displays online orders with the <strong>channel name WooCommerce</strong></li><li>POS orders display with the <strong>channel name POS</strong></li><li>Refunds initiated on the website by admins are also visible in the POS for the respective order</li></ul><p>This integration ensures complete visibility and synchronization between online and in-store sales, allowing admins and POS users to manage orders efficiently from a single platform.</p>',50)])])}]]),n=JSON.parse('{"path":"/woocommerce-pos/orders-drawers.html","title":"Orders & Cash Drawer","lang":"en-US","frontmatter":{"title":"Orders & Cash Drawer","description":"Manage POS orders, offline sales, refunds, and daily cash drawer operations.","sidebarPosition":8},"headers":[{"level":2,"title":"Processing POS Orders","slug":"processing-pos-orders","link":"#processing-pos-orders","children":[]},{"level":2,"title":"Adding Products to Cart","slug":"adding-products-to-cart","link":"#adding-products-to-cart","children":[{"level":3,"title":"Adding Custom Products","slug":"adding-custom-products","link":"#adding-custom-products","children":[]}]},{"level":2,"title":"Customer Management","slug":"customer-management","link":"#customer-management","children":[]},{"level":2,"title":"Checkout Process","slug":"checkout-process","link":"#checkout-process","children":[]},{"level":2,"title":"Applying Coupons & Discounts","slug":"applying-coupons-discounts","link":"#applying-coupons-discounts","children":[{"level":3,"title":"Coupons","slug":"coupons","link":"#coupons","children":[]},{"level":3,"title":"Discounts","slug":"discounts","link":"#discounts","children":[]}]},{"level":2,"title":"Offline Orders","slug":"offline-orders","link":"#offline-orders","children":[]},{"level":2,"title":"Order Management for Admins","slug":"order-management-for-admins","link":"#order-management-for-admins","children":[]},{"level":2,"title":"WooCommerce Website Orders","slug":"woocommerce-website-orders","link":"#woocommerce-website-orders","children":[]}],"git":{"contributors":[{"name":"himanshu","username":"","email":"himanshu.kumar731@webkul.in","commits":2},{"name":"harshit","username":"","email":"harshit.qa322@webkul.in","commits":1}],"changelog":[{"hash":"d40e6fdaa8b21bf16d0e572854cf43f79756c0c7","time":1768918927000,"email":"himanshu.kumar731@webkul.in","author":"himanshu","message":"Added: Update Code for POS doc"},{"hash":"0f78e3256fa0d58de79a9cbca0c15a253149691b","time":1767359090000,"email":"harshit.qa322@webkul.in","author":"harshit","message":"updated content file"},{"hash":"16518591e2894732d0b7035818abb4e0c6f620a6","time":1767082527000,"email":"himanshu.kumar731@webkul.in","author":"himanshu","message":"added initial commit"}]},"filePathRelative":"woocommerce-pos/orders-drawers.md"}')}}]);